Memo to @jimcramer @tomkeene @SquawkCNBC @cnbcfastmoney @ScottWapnerCNBC @andrewrsorkin @beckyquick I have a constructive suggestion for fin TV commentators... Don't look at Treasury rates - they tell you nothing about the problem Every company you interview or speak to you

should be asked the following: What has your borrowing cost risen to this week from a month ago? This is the immediate problem in a levered and indebted corporate society - that few are discussing. Look at Expedia, BBB rated (top if Investment Grade debt) - its implied
borrowing cost has risen from 3.2% to 7.2% in 4 weeks. @lizclaman @riskreversal @terranovajoe @guyadami The transmission of credit has been broken that is why the Fed is adopting such radical steps.
